						<div class="postbody">Yep,thanks I'm familiar with BLIT, BLEP, minBLEP and most other band limited synthesis techniques. I could also implement the APU's sound generation as quasi band limited direct digital synthesis (which is faster than any other band limited approach). But that is (at least for me) no option here.
<br />I want to emulate, not improve the NES sound, and the NES did it non band limited.
<br />Nevertheless I will have a look at blargg's library. Didn't know such thing existed and I'm always curious about new synthesis stuff <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /></div>

