					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">neet wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But, the NES does the following:<br />1. Generate non band limited digital audio (with aliasing)<br />2. Low pass filter it (aliasing ist still there!)</div>
<br />Let me guess: German?
<br />
<br />You could characterize the output of each APU channel as piecewise periodic, with the period and amplitude changing after each update usually once a frame. But if the period of a periodic signal divides evenly into the sample rate, which is the case with all PSGs in the APU, the aliases fall right back on the same frequencies. This means the aliasing is not only "nearly inaudible" but actually inaudible.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

